name: Union Pacific Coal GTEL
notes: Home-built experimental coal-fired gas turbine. Assembled from ALCO PA-1 UP #607, GN W1 #5018, and the tender from Challenger #3990. 215 feet (66 m) overall length; 1,457,280 pounds (661,011 kg) total weight. Unsuccessful; set aside in 1964 and scrapped in 1968.

name: H220
power: 3,600 HP / 2,680KW coal fired steam locomotive (50 mph) with 245KN tractive effort.
notes: The most powerful steam locomotive, at the time built in, Australia. 1 Built. Preserved at Newport, Victoria
